Typedef Documentation

◆ MatcherType

using proto::MatcherType = MatchStatus (*)(void*)

Maximum allowed field size in bytes.

Matcher callback type.

A matcher inspects the current field buffer and returns MatchStatus. Signature uses a raw pointer to the field storage; implementers should cast to the appropriate type for read-only checks. (The pointer is not owned and must not be stored.)

◆ FieldFlags

enum class proto::FieldFlags : uint8_t
strong

Bit flags describing protocol field properties.

Flags can be combined using bitwise operators. Use HasFlag for checks.

Enumerator
NOTHING 

No flags set.

IS_IN_LEN 

Field contributes to length calculation.

IS_IN_CRC 

Field contributes to CRC calculation.

REVERSE 

Field bytes are stored in reverse order.

SUPPRESS 

Field should be suppressed (hidden/skipped).

CONST_SIZE 

Field has a constant size.

◆ get_field_info_by_name()

template<FieldName NAME, typename Tuple, std::size_t Index = 0>
auto proto::get_field_info_by_name ( Tuple && tuple) -> decltype(auto)
constexpr

Retrieve a FieldInfo-like element from a tuple by its FieldName.

Callers should ensure at compile time that the tuple indeed contains the name, for example by using FieldInfoHasName before calling this function.

Template Parameters
NAMEFieldName to retrieve.
TupleTuple type.
IndexInternal recursion index (do not pass).
Parameters
tupleTuple instance.
Returns
Reference to the matching element inside the tuple.
Warning
If no element is found, the function reaches __builtin_unreachable(). Use FieldInfoHasName to guard calls in constant-evaluated contexts.
